# NextScan Design System Rules

> Cursor rules file. Place in `.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc` or project root as `.cursorrules`.
> Based on Vercel's Geist Design System, implemented via shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS.

---

## Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 15 (App Router)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4
- **Components:** shadcn/ui (new-york style, neutral base)
- **Font:** Geist Sans + Geist Mono via `geist` npm package
- **Icons:** Lucide React
- **Utilities:** `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` via `cn()` helper in `@/lib/utils`

---

## Typography

Use the Geist font family for everything. Never use system fonts or fallback stacks as primary.

### Setup

```tsx
// app/layout.tsx
import { GeistSans } from "geist/font/sans";
import { GeistMono } from "geist/font/mono";

export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en" className={`${GeistSans.variable} ${GeistMono.variable}`}>
      <body className="font-sans antialiased">{children}</body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

### Tailwind config

```css
/* globals.css — Tailwind v4 theme */
@theme {
  --font-sans: var(--font-geist-sans);
  --font-mono: var(--font-geist-mono);
}
```

### Type Scale

Follow the Geist typography hierarchy. Use these Tailwind classes:

**Headings** — use for page/section titles:

| Class | Size | Weight | Use |
|-------|------|--------|-----|
| `text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight` | 48px | 700 | Hero headline (one per page max) |
| `text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight` | 36px | 700 | Page title |
| `text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight` | 30px | 600 | Section heading |
| `text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight` | 24px | 600 | Card/panel heading |
| `text-xl font-semibold` | 20px | 600 | Sub-section heading |
| `text-lg font-medium` | 18px | 500 | Minor heading |

**Body copy** — use for paragraphs and multi-line text:

| Class | Size | Use |
|-------|------|-----|
| `text-base leading-7` | 16px | Default body text |
| `text-sm leading-6` | 14px | Secondary body text, descriptions |
| `text-xs leading-5` | 12px | Tertiary text, captions, fine print |

**Labels** — use for single-line UI text (buttons, badges, menus, form labels):

| Class | Size | Use |
|-------|------|-----|
| `text-sm font-medium` | 14px | Default label, nav items, form labels |
| `text-xs font-medium` | 12px | Badges, tags, helper text |
| `text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider` | 12px | Overline / eyebrow text |

**Mono** — use for data, codes, technical values:

| Class | Use |
|-------|-----|
| `font-mono text-sm` | Prices, reference numbers, clinic IDs |
| `font-mono text-xs` | Timestamps, coordinates |

### Rules

- Never use `font-bold` on body copy. Bold is for headings and `<strong>` emphasis only.
- Headings always use `tracking-tight` at sizes 24px and above.
- Body text uses default tracking (no letter-spacing override).
- Max content width for body copy: `max-w-prose` (~65ch).
- One `text-5xl` heading per page. Use `text-3xl` or `text-2xl` for most section headers.

