## Colors

Use CSS variables for all colors. Never hardcode hex values. The system uses semantic naming with light/dark mode support.

### Semantic Color Tokens

Define in `globals.css`. These map to shadcn/ui's expected token names:

```css
@layer base {
  :root {
    /* Backgrounds */
    --background: 0 0% 100%;          /* White — page background */
    --foreground: 0 0% 9%;            /* Near-black — primary text */

    /* Component surfaces */
    --card: 0 0% 100%;
    --card-foreground: 0 0% 9%;
    --popover: 0 0% 100%;
    --popover-foreground: 0 0% 9%;

    /* Primary action (teal/cyan for NextScan brand) */
    --primary: 174 72% 46%;
    --primary-foreground: 0 0% 100%;

    /* Secondary (muted actions) */
    --secondary: 0 0% 96%;
    --secondary-foreground: 0 0% 9%;

    /* Muted (subtle backgrounds, disabled states) */
    --muted: 0 0% 96%;
    --muted-foreground: 0 0% 45%;

    /* Accent (hover highlights) */
    --accent: 0 0% 96%;
    --accent-foreground: 0 0% 9%;

    /* Destructive (errors, warnings) */
    --destructive: 0 84% 60%;
    --destructive-foreground: 0 0% 100%;

    /* Borders and inputs */
    --border: 0 0% 90%;
    --input: 0 0% 90%;
    --ring: 174 72% 46%;              /* Focus ring matches primary */

    /* Border radius */
    --radius: 0.5rem;                 /* 8px default corner radius */
  }

  .dark {
    --background: 0 0% 4%;
    --foreground: 0 0% 95%;
    --card: 0 0% 7%;
    --card-foreground: 0 0% 95%;
    --popover: 0 0% 7%;
    --popover-foreground: 0 0% 95%;
    --primary: 174 72% 46%;
    --primary-foreground: 0 0% 100%;
    --secondary: 0 0% 15%;
    --secondary-foreground: 0 0% 95%;
    --muted: 0 0% 15%;
    --muted-foreground: 0 0% 64%;
    --accent: 0 0% 15%;
    --accent-foreground: 0 0% 95%;
    --destructive: 0 62% 50%;
    --destructive-foreground: 0 0% 95%;
    --border: 0 0% 15%;
    --input: 0 0% 15%;
    --ring: 174 72% 46%;
    --radius: 0.5rem;
  }
}
```

### Functional Color Classes

Use Tailwind's semantic classes which map to the CSS variables above:

| Purpose | Tailwind class | Token |
|---------|---------------|-------|
| Page background | `bg-background` | `--background` |
| Primary text | `text-foreground` | `--foreground` |
| Secondary text | `text-muted-foreground` | `--muted-foreground` |
| Primary button bg | `bg-primary` | `--primary` |
| Primary button text | `text-primary-foreground` | `--primary-foreground` |
| Card surface | `bg-card` | `--card` |
| Borders | `border-border` | `--border` |
| Input borders | `border-input` | `--input` |
| Focus ring | `ring-ring` | `--ring` |
| Error/destructive | `bg-destructive` | `--destructive` |
| Subtle bg (badges, tags) | `bg-muted` | `--muted` |

### Rules

- Never use raw color values like `bg-gray-100` or `text-black`. Always use semantic tokens.
- `text-foreground` for primary text. `text-muted-foreground` for secondary/helper text.
- The NextScan brand color is teal/cyan (`hsl(174, 72%, 46%)`). This is `--primary`.
- Use `bg-muted` for subtle differentiation. Use `bg-card` for elevated surfaces.
- Error states use `destructive`. Success states use a green override: `text-emerald-600`.
- Focus states: `focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2`

