## Layout Patterns

### Page structure

```tsx
<main className="min-h-screen bg-background">
  <nav>{/* sticky top nav */}</nav>
  <div className="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    {/* page content */}
  </div>
  <footer>{/* site footer */}</footer>
</main>
```

### Booking flow layout

- Container: `max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4`
- Step indicator at top using `Progress` component
- Each step is a full-width card or section
- Navigation: `flex justify-between` with Back (ghost) and Continue (primary) buttons
- Mobile: single column, full-width inputs, `min-h-[44px]` touch targets

### Card grid (clinic list)

```tsx
<div className="space-y-4">
  {clinics.map(clinic => (
    <Card key={clinic.id} className="cursor-pointer hover:border-primary transition-colors">
      {/* clinic card content */}
    </Card>
  ))}
</div>
```

- Clinic cards: stack vertically (never grid on mobile). Use `space-y-4`.
- Each card: `p-6`, `rounded-lg` (uses `--radius`), `border` default.
- Hover: `hover:border-primary` to indicate interactivity.
- Selected: `border-primary ring-2 ring-primary/20` to show active state.

### Responsive breakpoints

| Breakpoint | Width | Use |
|-----------|-------|-----|
| Default (mobile) | < 640px | Single column, stacked layout |
| `sm` | 640px | Minor adjustments |
| `md` | 768px | 2-column options where appropriate |
| `lg` | 1024px | Full desktop layout |

Design mobile-first. All components must work at 320px minimum width.

