## Patterns for NextScan

### Selectable option cards (scan type, body area, region)

```tsx
<button
  onClick={() => onSelect(option.id)}
  className={cn(
    "w-full text-left rounded-lg border p-4 transition-colors",
    "hover:border-primary hover:bg-accent",
    selected === option.id
      ? "border-primary bg-primary/5 ring-2 ring-primary/20"
      : "border-border bg-card"
  )}
>
  <div className="text-sm font-medium">{option.name}</div>
  <div className="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-1">{option.description}</div>
</button>
```

### Star rating display

```tsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-1.5">
  <Star className="h-4 w-4 fill-amber-400 text-amber-400" />
  <span className="text-sm font-medium">{rating}</span>
  <span className="text-xs text-muted-foreground">({reviewCount} reviews)</span>
</div>
```

### Trust/compliance badges

```tsx
<div className="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-xs text-muted-foreground">
  <Badge variant="outline" className="gap-1">
    <Shield className="h-3 w-3" /> Not a clinic
  </Badge>
  <Badge variant="outline" className="gap-1">
    <Lock className="h-3 w-3" /> PHIPA-aligned
  </Badge>
</div>
```

### Form section separator

```tsx
<Separator className="my-6" />
```

### Empty state (e.g., no clinics found)

```tsx
<div className="text-center py-12">
  <Search className="h-10 w-10 text-muted-foreground mx-auto mb-4" />
  <h3 className="text-lg font-medium">No clinics found</h3>
  <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-2 max-w-sm mx-auto">
    Try expanding your region filters to see more options.
  </p>
  <Button variant="outline" className="mt-4" onClick={expandFilters}>
    Show all regions
  </Button>
</div>
```

